reviewText: This is a high-quality collection of Rocky Jones DVDs at a great price. If you like really sappy 1950s space science fiction done really well, this collection is for you. Don't pass it up.

If should be noted that the 6 DVD set does NOT have a box.  The six Alpha cases are simply shrink wrapped into one sales unit with a label on it.  It was still cheaper to buy them this way, however.

Only Menace From Outer Space pictured was DVD, the rest were DVD-R.  Menace also has the lowest catalog number.
Great to watch remember this from when I was a kid
Oh what memories this brings back!
Some people complain about the special effects in this series. THERE WAS NO CGI. They did their best. The story is good, so is the acting.  Just plain fun!

Very nice to view the old material.  I enjoyed the simple special effects and the rocket designs because I am a model rocket hobbyist.  The video quality is very substandard compared to even older movies from the 40's.
This was one of the earliest TV shows of space and the future.  A lot of fun to see these programs again.
